----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 5. Core Components of MCP


ğŸ”¹ 5.1 MCP Client

* Runs alongside the AI model
* Sends structured requests
* Receives tool results

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.2 MCP Server

* Exposes tools and data
* Handles permissions
* Executes actions safely

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.3 Tools

* Functions
* APIs
* Databases
* File systems
* Web services

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”¹ 5.4 Context

* Inputs
* Outputs
* Memory
* Tool results

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“Œ 6. How MCP Works (Step-by-Step)

1. Model decides it needs a tool
2. MCP Client sends request
3. MCP Server validates request
4. Tool is executed
5. Result is returned to model
6. Model continues reasoning

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

